<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="25" pageNumber="525" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1899,2035]" lastBlockId="26.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="25" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,513,1935,1960]" pageId="25" pageNumber="525">Diagnosis. Female imago:</emphasis>
1) forewing with pigmented C, Sc and R1 areas, extending beyond R1 but not forming bands (
<figureCitation box="[329,411,1974,1999]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="525">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
C); 2) forewing with thick cross veins in C and Sc areas (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1137,1974,1999]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="525">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
C); 3) marginal intercalary veins single (
<figureCitation box="[316,405,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="525">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
C); 4) hind wing with one intercalary marginal vein (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1161,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="525">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
C); 5) hind wing with quadrangular costal process; 6) body covered with brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[900,986,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
B); 7) anterolateral spots on abdominal terga and sterna present (
<figureCitation box="[431,513,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1210,1442,1464]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" targetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" targetPageId="26">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1210,1442,1464]" box="[151,1210,1442,1464]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1442,1464]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">FIGURE 19.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[293,505,1442,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Callibaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viviparus">
<emphasis box="[293,505,1442,1464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Callibaetis viviparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1503,2000]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,830,1503,1528]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Complementary description. Female imago: Thorax.</emphasis>
Covered with brownish spots. Wings. Forewing (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
C) pigmentation extending beyond R1 but not forming bands; veins light brown; C, Sc and R1 areas with thick cross veins; stigmatic area with 2–3 cross veins touching and 3–4 not touching subcostal vein; marginal intercalary veins single; length of each intercalary vein 0.41 × distance between adjacent longitudinal veins; length of forewing about 2.4 × width. Hind wing hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[704,785,1650,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
C) and with 14 cross veins; one intercalary marginal vein present. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[252,377,1686,1711]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Terga covered with brown spots, with spot anterolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1194,1686,1711]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
B). Sterna with spot anterolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[328,410,1722,1747]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,271,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[182,1403,267,1418]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Callibaetis viviparus female imago (holotype). A. label; B. dorsal view of body; C. wings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292693/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
B). Caudal filaments lost.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="526" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1503,2000]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1758,1783]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vinasco-Mondragon" box="[345,781,1758,1783]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" refString="Vinasco-Mondragon, A. F. &amp; Zuniga, M. D. C. (2016) Primeros registros de Callibaetis radiatus y C. viviparus (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae) para Colombia. Revista Colombiana de Entomologia, 42 (1), 91 - 94." type="journal article" year="2016">Vinasco-Mondragón &amp; Zúñiga (2016)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName box="[899,1039,1759,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Callibaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viviparus">
<emphasis box="[899,1039,1759,1783]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">C. viviparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1100,1283,1759,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Callibaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radiatus" subGenus="Callibaetis">
<emphasis box="[1100,1126,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1145,1171,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1190,1283,1759,1783]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">radiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1325,1435,1758,1783]" name="Colombia" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Colombia</collectingCountry>
based on female imagoes. The morphological evidence to differentiate both species was the shape of the costal process of the hind wing (round in 
<taxonomicName box="[556,695,1831,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Callibaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viviparus">
<emphasis box="[556,695,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">C. viviparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and truncante or quadrangular in 
<taxonomicName box="[1086,1266,1831,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Callibaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radiatus" subGenus="Callibaetis">
<emphasis box="[1086,1112,1831,1854]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1130,1155,1831,1854]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1173,1266,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">radiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Studying the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1866,1891]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[290,428,1867,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Callibaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viviparus">
<emphasis box="[290,428,1867,1890]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">C. viviparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(mounted on a slide), we observed that one peak of the costal process is turned inward, appearing to be rounded. Thus, the morphological evidence presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinasco-Mondragon" box="[1001,1436,1902,1927]" pageId="26" pageNumber="526" refString="Vinasco-Mondragon, A. F. &amp; Zuniga, M. D. C. (2016) Primeros registros de Callibaetis radiatus y C. viviparus (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae) para Colombia. Revista Colombiana de Entomologia, 42 (1), 91 - 94." type="journal article" year="2016">Vinasco-Mondragón &amp; Zúñiga (2016)</bibRefCitation>
and Cruz 
<emphasis box="[260,317,1939,1963]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">et al.</emphasis>
(2014) is not corroborated, not allowing the differentiation of both species. Taking into account the new evidence, association between stages should be made in order to confirm or refute the records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1319,1433,1974,1999]" name="Colombia" pageId="26" pageNumber="526">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
